_Huf’al_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_Huf’al_ past tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                              | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | הֻבְדַּלְתִּי<br>_huvdalti_<br>I was separated | \<       | הֻבְדַּלְנוּ<br>_huvdalnu_<br>We were seperated | \< |
| *Second-Person* | הֻבְדַּלְתָּ <br>_huvdaltau_<br> You [male] were separated | הֻבְדַּלְתְּ <br>_huvdalt_<br> You [female] were separated  | הֻבְדַּלְתֶּם <br>_huvdaltem_<br> You [males] were separated  | הֻבְדַּלְתֶּן <br>_huvdalten_<br> You [females] were separated |
| *Third-Person* | הֻבְדַּל <br>_huvdal_<br> He were separated | הֻבְדְּלָה <br>_huvdelau_<br> She were separated  | הֻבְדְּלוּ <br>_huvdelu_<br> They [male or female] were separated  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ב, ‎ד, and ל above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
